63
00:02:38,360 --> 00:02:39,000
Students,

64
00:02:39,840 --> 00:02:42,199
Hainan is a blessed land for us agriculture students.

65
00:02:42,479 --> 00:02:43,599
Look at that patch behind us.

66
00:02:43,840 --> 00:02:45,000
That's the jackfruit experimental field.

67
00:02:45,840 --> 00:02:48,439
Further back is the hybrid rice experimental field.

68
00:02:49,080 --> 00:02:50,400
The significance of this land,

69
00:02:50,759 --> 00:02:51,759
we all know in our hearts.

70
00:02:53,759 --> 00:02:54,520
Can't see it, right?

71
00:02:56,199 --> 00:02:57,159
It's fine if you can't see it.

72
00:02:57,479 --> 00:02:58,680
I'll take you to see it later.

73
00:02:59,000 --> 00:02:59,639
Back to business.

74
00:03:00,280 --> 00:03:00,960
Three years ago,

75
00:03:01,680 --> 00:03:03,120
when I came to Hainan for research,

76
00:03:03,560 --> 00:03:04,520
I discovered a type of

77
00:03:04,680 --> 00:03:07,120
tree with natural insect-repelling abilities.

78
00:03:07,479 --> 00:03:08,400
At that time, we

79
00:03:08,520 --> 00:03:10,039
wore out seven or eight pairs of boots walking.

80
00:03:10,319 --> 00:03:11,960
So, we gave this tree a name.

81
00:03:11,960 --> 00:03:12,879
It's called the Boot Tree.

82
00:03:13,759 --> 00:03:14,800
Boot Tree. Boots.

83
00:03:14,800 --> 00:03:15,680
Over these three years,

84
00:03:15,919 --> 00:03:17,159
one of my research topics

85
00:03:17,639 --> 00:03:19,759
has been the papaya tree and Boot Tree's

86
00:03:19,759 --> 00:03:20,759
new hybrid variety.

87
00:03:21,240 --> 00:03:21,719
Right here.

88
00:03:23,039 --> 00:03:24,120
This new variety

89
00:03:24,439 --> 00:03:25,159
not only retains

90
00:03:25,159 --> 00:03:27,039
the original texture and taste of papaya,

91
00:03:27,319 --> 00:03:28,080
but also

92
00:03:28,080 --> 00:03:30,360
solves the common problem in papaya trees:

93
00:03:30,439 --> 00:03:31,479
