94
00:03:31,639 --> 00:03:32,680
As you can see with the naked eye,

95
00:03:32,879 --> 00:03:33,759
the previous trees

96
00:03:33,960 --> 00:03:35,080
lost their green and turned white.

97
00:03:35,240 --> 00:03:36,879
But now, in our experimental field,

98
00:03:37,240 --> 00:03:38,120
it's a lush green patch.

99
00:03:39,159 --> 00:03:39,599
Yeah.

100
00:03:41,120 --> 00:03:41,479
For sure.

101
00:03:41,479 --> 00:03:43,360
It means we calculate the leaf chlorosis area.

102
00:03:43,960 --> 00:03:45,439
No need to touch bugs anymore.

103
00:03:46,120 --> 00:03:46,639
Really.

104
00:03:46,879 --> 00:03:47,479
Undergraduates,

105
00:03:47,680 --> 00:03:48,599
third year and above,

106
00:03:48,599 --> 00:03:49,879
and graduate students,

107
00:03:50,199 --> 00:03:52,599
group up to calculate the leaf chlorosis area.

108
00:03:53,000 --> 00:03:54,800
First and second-year undergraduates,

109
00:03:55,039 --> 00:03:56,479
record the standard plant count.

110
00:03:56,479 --> 00:03:58,759
In all four directions,

111
00:03:58,960 --> 00:04:01,120
